Ok, goddamnit, +1. The imagery in many places was quite interesting, and those couple of wham lines (you make us look like the bad guys, I don't know how to fix a god, we've got a war to win), just. wham.

I was holding onto my novote for quite a while there, though. The main problem is that you're often un-economical with your writing, particularly when writing in clinical tone. You're very often repeating details we've read one or two paragraphs back. This also happens every time you start a new document, section, or log, where things would logically be repeated in a real document, but I've already read it once, I get it. You've already got a lot of narrative and imagery that you're asking us to work through, don't make me feel like you're wasting my time when there is cool stuff to get to.





